1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 Be7 6. Bg2 O-O 7. O-O Nbd7 8.
Qb3 {This is the second most popular move. As in the main line with 8.Qc2,
from b3 the queen also protects the c4-pawn. It appears to be more active,
pressuring b7 and d5 and thus preventing ...Ne4 for the moment, but also loses
some resources, like the quick advance of the pawns in this sector.} c6 {
A solid choice and also the most frequent one in practice.} ({Black also has
good results with the alternative} 8... Nb6 {, an idea first played by
Vereslav Eingorn. The critical line runs} 9. c5 Nc4 10. Qc2 (10. Bf4 b6 11. c6
a5 12. Qc2 {[Huang Qian - Zhai Mo, China rapid 2018]} Ne4 $13) (10. Na3 Nxd2
11. Nxd2 c6 {, giving Black easy equality, as in Dragnev - Alekseenko, Skopje
2019.}) 10... b6 11. c6 (11. b3 Nxd2 12. Nbxd2 bxc5 13. dxc5 c6 $11 {Nakamura
- Kasimdzhanov, Bastia rapid 2007}) (11. Bf4 bxc5 12. b3 {[Gleizerov -
Naroditsky, Riga 2013]} Nd6 13. dxc5 Nde4 $11) 11... a5 {and now} 12. Bf4 (12.
Nc3 Ba6 13. a4 {[Gleizerov - Fantinel, Las Palmas 2019]} Qd6 $5 {is fine for
Black, for instance:} 14. Nb5 Bxb5 15. axb5 Nxd2 16. Qxd2 Ne4 17. Qc2 Qb4 $36)
(12. b3 Nxd2 (12... Nd6 $5) 13. Nbxd2 Ba6 14. Rfe1 a4 $5 (14... Ba3 $11) 15.
bxa4 {(Pogonina - Pashikian, Yerevan 2018)} Bb4 $44) 12... Ba6 (12... Ne4 $5)
13. Rd1 {(Ding Liren - Karjakin, Cupar rapid 2019)} Ne4 ({or} 13... Bd6 $5) 14.
a4 f6 $13 {offers chances for both sides}) ({Black can also consider} 8... a5 {
, as in Yuffa - Fressinet, Skopje 2019.}) 9. Nc3 {This developing move is of
similar value as the main alternatives. I use it as main line because is the
most popular. Now several moves deserve consideration:} ({a)} 9. Bb4 {is a
strategically correct idea, but not sufficient for an advantage:} b6 (9... Bxb4
10. Qxb4 a5 {is an alternative, as in Kozul - Kuljasevic, Croatia 2017}) 10.
Bxe7 (10. cxd5 cxd5 11. Nc3 Bxb4 12. Qxb4 a5 13. Qb3 Ba6 14. Rfc1 Qe7 $11 {
Medvegy - Doettling, Germany 2008}) 10... Qxe7 11. Nc3 Bb7 (11... a5 $5 {
Andersson - Georgiadis, Gibraltar 2014}) 12. cxd5 (12. Rac1 Rac8 13. Rfd1 dxc4
14. Qxc4 c5 15. Ne1 Bxg2 16. Nxg2 cxd4 $11 {, and a draw was declared in
Andersson - Jussupow, Germany 2003.}) 12... cxd5 (12... exd5 $5) 13. Rfc1 Rfc8
14. e3 {(Grabarczik - Nguyen, Praga 2009)} Nb8 $5 $13 {followed by ...Nc6} (
14... Ne4 {is another try here.})) ({b)} 9. Rc1 a5 {This expansion is standard
against the queen on b3.} (9... Ne4 $5 {Ljubojevic - Jussupow, Rotterdam 1989})
10. a4 (10. Bg5 h6 11. Bxf6 Bxf6 12. Na3 Qe7 $11 {Le Quang - Adams, Tromso ol
2014}) 10... h6 11. Be1 Bd6 12. Bc3 b6 13. Nbd2 Bb7 14. Qc2 c5 $11 {
Papaioannou - Georgiadis 2014}) ({c)} 9. Bf4 a5 (9... Ne4 10. Nc3 (10. h4 h6
11. Nfd2 g5 12. hxg5 hxg5 $13 {Meskovs - Ruiz, Voronezh 2019}) 10... g5 11. Be3
Nd6 12. cxd5 exd5 13. Rad1 f5 $132 {Gelfand - Andreikin, Hengshui 2019}) 10.
Rd1 (10. Rc1 h6 11. a4 Ne4 12. Nfd2 Nd6 13. Bxd6 Bxd6 14. e4 dxe4 15. Nxe4 Bb4
$11 {Giri - Aronian, Istambul ol 2012}) 10... Nh5 (10... h6 $5 {Gelfand - Giri,
Amsterdam blitz 2019}) 11. Bc1 Nhf6 (11... b5 $5 12. cxb5 a4 13. Qc2 cxb5 14.
e4 Nhf6 15. e5 Ne4 $132) 12. Nbd2 b5 13. c5 (13. cxb5 cxb5 $15) 13... b4 (13...
Qc7 $5) 14. Qc2 a4 $132 {Caruana - So, Berlin ct 2018}) ({d)} 9. Rd1 {is again
answered with} a5 {Then} 10. Bf4 b5 11. c5 Nh5 12. Bc1 {was played in Yuffa -
Sethuraman, Moscow 2019, where} Qc7 {is close to balanced.}) ({e)} 9. Bg5 b6 (
9... a5 $5) (9... b5 $5) 10. Rd1 {is Krasenkow - Donchenko, Porticcio 2019.
The most energetic move now is} Ba6 $5 11. Nfd2 c5 (11... b5 $5) 12. dxc5 Nxc5
13. Qa3 h6 14. Bxf6 Bxf6 $13) 9... Nb6 {Provoking White to close the queenside.
} (9... a5 $5 {, as in Ftacnik - Parligras, Tromso ol 2014, is a reasonable
alternative here, that can lead to lines from the previous note.}) 10. c5 (10.
cxd5 exd5 11. Ne5 Bf5 $11 {Bosiocic - Brkic, Croatia ch 2018}) 10... Nc4 11.
Bf4 (11. Qc2 {is the main alternative to text. After} b6 {(Korchnoi's move)}
12. b4 a5 13. a3 Ba6 {a position with chances for both sides arises. A
possible line is} 14. Rfb1 bxc5 15. bxc5 {(Verduga - Nikolac, Almada 1988)} h6
16. Na4 Nd7 $13) 11... b6 12. Na4 $5 {Alternatives are:} ({a)} 12. cxb6 axb6
13. Qc2 (13. Rfd1 Ba6 $36 {is comfortable for the second player, as in Flear -
Tiviakov, Corsica rapid 1997.}) 13... c5 14. b3 Na3 15. Qb2 Bd7 $11 {Huhndorf
- Trella, Alemanha 2006}) ({b)} 12. Qa4 $6 Nxb2 13. Qxc6 Ba6 {The white queen
is in trouble:} 14. Rfb1 {(Nguyen Van Huy - Zhou Jianchao, Ho Chi Minh City
2012)} Rc8 15. Ne5 Bxc5 16. dxc5 Rxc6 17. Nxc6 Qe8 $17) 12... Nd7 (12... Ba6 $5
{Ekeberg - Ostenstad, Norway 2008}) 13. Qc3 bxc5 14. b3 Ncb6 15. Nxc5 Nxc5 16.
dxc5 Nd7 $11 {Onischuk - Dautov, Germany 2001. The black centre compensates
for the activity of the white pieces.} *

