1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. g3 $5 {In this and the next chapters we will see White
using other move-orders that White has at his disposal. While they are not
dangerous for the second player, sometimes they lead to situations where our
recommended lines from the previous chapters can't be played. In that case,
here comes our plan B.} Nf6 {Natural and in accordance with our repertoire.} ({
The reader can also investigate a more independent try like} 3... dxc4 4. Bg2 (
{or} 4. Nf3 c5) 4... c5 $13) 4. Bg2 Bb4+ 5. Nd2 {White is trying to achieve an
independent position. The alternatives are} ({a)} 5. Bd2 Be7 6. Nc3 (6. Nf3 {
transposes to positions viewed in the previous chapters}) (6. Qc2 O-O {, when
7.Nf3 again leads to well-known positions, while} 7. e3 b6 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Ne2
{[Kramnik-Grischuk, Moscow blitz 2010]} c6 {is satisfactory for Black}) 6...
O-O 7. cxd5 (7. Qb3 {can be answered with 7...c6 or} Nc6 $5) 7... exd5 8. e3 c6
9. Nge2 {While White successfully reaches an independent position, this poses
no problems for Black:} Na6 10. O-O Nc7 11. f3 Ne6 12. Kh1 b6 13. Be1 {Draw
declared in Nogueiras - Chernin, Montpellier ct 1985. Black can continue with}
c5 14. Bf2 Re8 $11 {with chances for both sides.}) ({b)} 5. Nc3 {Now 5...dxc4
isn't possible due to the check on a4, but Black can simply castle.} O-O {
Now after the usual 6.Nf3, he replies 6...dxc4, transposing to chapter 1.
Instead, White can play} 6. a3 {, where after} Bxc3+ (6... Be7 {is also good.})
7. bxc3 dxc4 {A fashionable continuation.} 8. Nf3 (8. Qa4 Bd7 9. Qxc4 Bc6 10.
f3 Qd7 $5 11. Rb1 Bd5 12. Qd3 Qc6 $13 {Ponomariov - Kravtsiv, Ukraine ch 2018})
8... c5 9. O-O Nc6 {Black doesn't have any problems:} 10. a4 (10. Qc2 cxd4 11.
cxd4 Nxd4 12. Nxd4 Qxd4 13. Bb2 Qc5 14. Rfd1 e5 15. a4 Re8 {Damjanovic -
Trifunovic, Ljubljana 1960. White has sufficient compensation at best.}) (10.
dxc5 $5 Qxd1 11. Rxd1 Ne4 12. Bf4 Nxc3 13. Rd2 Ne4 14. Rc2 Nxc5 15. Rxc4 Nd7 {
with the same evaluation as in the previous line.}) 10... Qa5 (10... Na5 $5)
11. Qc2 Rd8 12. Rd1 (12. Bd2 Qc7 13. dxc5 h6 14. Nd4 Na5 $11 {Bukal - Berescu,
