Bxe5 O-O 14. Re1 Rc8 15. a5 $36) 10. Nxc5 Bd5 11. Bg5 O-O 12. Rc1 Nbd7 13. Nxd7
Qxd7 14. Ne5 Qb7 15. f3 Ng4 (15... h6 16. Bd2 a5 17. e4 c3 {is an option} 18.
bxc3 Ba2 19. Ra1 b3 20. Nd3 Nd7 $44) 16. Bxe7 Ne3 17. Qd2 Nxf1 18. Qxb4 Rfe8 (
18... Rfb8 $5) 19. Qxb7 Bxb7 20. Bb4 Ne3 21. Bh3 Ba6 $11) ({b)} 9. Ne5 cxd4 10.
Nb3 O-O 11. Nxd4 Bd6 12. Nd3 Qd7 13. c5 (13. Bf4 Bxf4 14. gxf4 Rc8 15. Ne5 Qe7
$13) 13... Be7 14. Bf4 (14. Ne5 Qc8 15. Bf4 Qxc5 16. Rc1 Qb6 17. Be3 Qd8 {
White has compensation, but no more than that.}) 14... Nc6 15. Nxc6 Bxc6 16.
Nxb4 Bxc5 17. Nxc6 Qxc6 18. Be5 Rac8 (18... Nd7 $5) (18... Be7 $5) 19. e3 (19.
Bxf6 gxf6 20. e4 dxe4 21. Qg4+ Kh8 22. Qh4 f5 23. Qf6+ Kg8 $11) 19... Nd7 20.
Bc3 Be7 $11) ({c)} 9. Re1 {isn't dangerous here:} dxc4 10. Nxc4 Bd5 11. Nce5 (
11. Nfe5 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 {, and now} Qd5+ {shows the difference to the line from
the previous note.}) 11... O-O 12. dxc5 Bxc5 13. Nd3 Be7 $11) ({d)} 9. cxd5
Bxd5 10. dxc5 Nbd7 11. e4 $5 Nxe4 12. Nxe4 Bxe4 13. Qd4 (13. Qe2 Nxc5 14. Qb5+
Kf8 15. Be3 Bd3 16. Qxb4 Bxf1 17. Kxf1 $44) 13... Nf6 14. Be3 Qxd4 15. Bxd4 O-O
16. Nd2 Bxg2 17. Kxg2 Rac8 18. Rac1 Nd5 $11) 9... O-O {The c5-pawn doesn't run
away.} (9... Nbd7 10. c6 (10. a5 dxc4 11. Nxc4 O-O 12. a6 Bd5 13. c6 Bxc6 14.
Be3 Bd5 $11) (10. cxd5 Bxd5 {transposes to 9.cxd5}) 10... Bxc6 11. Nd4 Bb7 12.
a5 $36) 10. Ne5 (10. cxd5 Bxd5 11. Nb3 Na6 12. Be3 Rc8 13. Rc1 Nd7 14. c6 Rxc6
15. Rxc6 Bxc6 16. Qd2 (16. Bxa7 Bxa4 $11) 16... Bxa4 (16... Bf6 17. Ra1 Bd5 18.
Nfd4 Ne5 $13) 17. Ra1 Bxb3 18. Rxa6 Bc5 $11) (10. Nd4 Bxc5 11. N2b3 Be7 12. Bf4
Nc6 $11) 10... Bxc5 {Now this is necessary.} 11. Nb3 (11. cxd5 Bxd5 12. Nb3 Bd6
$11) (11. Nd3 Be7 $11) 11... Bd6 {This is better than the somewhat passive} (
11... Be7 12. Nd4 (12. a5 Qc8 13. a6 $5 Nxa6 14. Na5 Bd8 15. Nxb7 Qxb7 16. cxd5
exd5 17. Nc4 Nc7 $11 {White has compensation, but no more than that.}) (12.
cxd5 Nxd5 $11) 12... Qc8 13. cxd5 Nxd5 (13... Bxd5 14. Nf5 $36) 14. a5 (14. e4
Nf6 15. Qe2 Qc5 $11) 14... Nf6 15. Qa4 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 Qb7+ 17. Ndf3 $14) 12. Nd3
(12. Qd4 Bxe5 13. Qxe5 Nc6 (13... Nbd7 14. Qd6) 14. Qe3 Ba6 15. cxd5 Nxd5 16.
Qc5 Rc8 17. Re1 Re8 $11) (12. Bf4 g5 13. c5 Bc7 14. Na5 Qc8 15. Nxb7 Qxb7 16.
c6 Nxc6 17. Nxc6 gxf4 18. Rc1 Bd6 $11) 12... Nbd7 13. c5 Be7 14. a5 Rc8 15. a6
Ba8 16. Bd2 (16. Be3 e5 $11) 16... Ne4 17. Bxb4 Nexc5 $11 {With roughly equal
play. My analysis shows that the line 8...Be7 is a decent alternative to the
more common tries and deserves to be tried in practice.} *

