{[#] TEST 14 - What idea offers Black enterprising play here?} 10... g5 $1 {
Standard in this variation and in this type of positions, winning space on the
kingside with gain of tempo on the opponent's dark-squared bishop. Usually
Black continues with . ..f5, solidifying the e4-square, or, when the
threatened bishop retreats to e3, with the manoeuvre ...Nd6. Now a recent
example is} 11. Be3 Nd6 12. cxd5 exd5 {Black's position is more than fine, as
in Ramos - Robson, Batumi ol 2018.} *

